1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,640
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:03,440
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,180
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:07,610
For you,

5
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:10,010
I'll make them all pay.

6
00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:12,650
Jin Ju, I'll make them suffer
1,000 times more...

7
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:14,720
than you ever suffered.

8
00:00:17,220 --> 00:00:21,360
- I...
- I'll make it worse than death!

9
00:00:24,860 --> 00:00:25,860
No!

10
00:00:32,540 --> 00:00:34,070
I had no other choice.

11
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:38,810
You don't know anything.

12
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:41,480
You should just...

13
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,750
stay out of it and do nothing.

14
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:48,550
You can never get revenge for her,

15
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,520
and you'll never win.

16
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:02,070
You had no choice?

17
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,970
You're saying it wasn't an accident,

18
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,870
but you had no choice?

19
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:12,210
What?

20
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,080
Park Min Jun.

21
00:01:16,650 --> 00:01:18,780
Wait, was this intentional?

22
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:24,360
The person who forced your hand,

23
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:27,230
who I can't get revenge on
or defeat.

24
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:30,030
It's my father, isn't it?

25
00:01:32,030 --> 00:01:33,530
The car accident
from seven years ago.

26
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:36,330
It wasn't just an accident.

27
00:01:37,740 --> 00:01:38,770
My father...

28
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:42,210
My father!

29
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:47,580
That's what you've been hiding,
isn't it?

30
00:01:50,980 --> 00:01:51,980
I...

31
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,390
I don't know anything.

32
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,520
You said...

33
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:00,230
that I was your compensation.

34
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,800
That means you're involved
in the accident too.

35
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:12,770
I've already figured it all out.

36
00:02:50,010 --> 00:02:52,710
You just fell for Temi Bio's...

37
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,410
slick marketing.

38
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:58,550
The CEO was a con man,

39
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:02,050
an expert at embezzlement
and deception.

40
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:05,520
He was irresponsible...

41
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:09,830
and cowardly, right to the very end.

42
00:03:13,430 --> 00:03:15,630
How could he say that
to Jin Ju's face?

43
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,040
How could a person...

44
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:24,980
How could he?

45
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,510
I'm sorry.

46
00:03:58,880 --> 00:03:59,880
I'm so sorry.

47
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:06,050
I didn't know why you became Chloe,

48
00:04:07,290 --> 00:04:09,850
or what you must have felt
when you returned.

49
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:16,390
But I had the nerve...

50
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:20,430
I actually dared to think...

51
00:04:24,670 --> 00:04:26,770
that I could get
the real Jin Ju back.

52
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,710
Mr. Park.

53
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:35,880
I...

54
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:00,410
I'm so sorry
it took me this long to find out.

55
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:04,940
The person who caused
the accident seven years ago...

56
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,880
The person who brutally
murdered your father...

57
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,220
I can't believe it was my father.

58
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,890
It was my own father.

59
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:35,440
Don't you ever forgive him.
Actually, no.

60
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:39,210
I'm the one who can't forgive him.

61
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,780
I'll expose what happened
seven years ago...

62
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:46,080
and make him...

63
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:48,990
beg you for forgiveness.

64
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:58,160
And how are you going to do that?

65
00:06:05,670 --> 00:06:06,670
What...

66
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:10,580
could you possibly do?

67
00:06:14,650 --> 00:06:15,780
After all,

68
00:06:17,450 --> 00:06:19,750
you're nothing
but Chairman Park Tae Ho's son.

69
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:24,890
Baek Jin Ju.

70
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:38,740
Park Min Jun.

71
00:06:40,170 --> 00:06:41,670
Did he plan this from the beginning,

72
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:43,670
just to confirm his suspicions?

73
00:06:46,710 --> 00:06:48,510
Did he run straight
to Chairman Park?

74
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:55,390
No.

75
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:57,460
If he had,
Chairman Park would be after me.

76
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,560
Right,

77
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:06,130
I still have a chance.

78
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,540
I have to silence Min Jun...

79
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,210
and get something out
of Chairman Park quickly.

80
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:17,940
But how?

81
00:07:18,580 --> 00:07:20,440
How do I silence Min Jun?

82
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:35,990
The explosion staged
to look like a car accident,

83
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,560
the forged suicide note and ledgers,

84
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,360
the hastily closed investigation,

85
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:45,800
and the collusion between Choi Yu Na
and President Choi Sam Sik.

86
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,170
It was all...

87
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:51,110
orchestrated
by Chairman Park Tae Ho.

88
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,150
I barely survived,

89
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,750
so I became Chloe to get my revenge.

90
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:01,450
You could've told me.

91
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:12,360
You, when you're
Chairman Park Tae Ho's son?

92
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,830
Your father...

93
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:21,270
is the man who murdered my dad
and covered it up with lies.

94
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:25,480
And you think
you can make him face justice?

95
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:28,750
Do you really think
you have that kind of power?

96
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:33,450
Seven years ago, and even now,

97
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,850
you're completely powerless!

98
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,160
Me?

99
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:43,730
For the past seven years,

100
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,360
I've lived for nothing but revenge.

101
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,130
I fought my way back here,

102
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:51,370
and I'm nearing the end
through agony.

103
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:56,140
You finding out who I am
and learning of your dad's crimes?

104
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,810
That was never part of my plan!

105
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:01,080
Anything you do now...

106
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:04,850
will only stand in the way
of my revenge.

107
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:08,320
That guilt you're feeling?

108
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:09,790
Just please!

109
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:12,560
Deal with it on your own.

110
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:15,990
For whatever reason,

111
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:20,130
don't ruin my revenge
and seven years...

112
00:09:22,570 --> 00:09:24,000
of waiting.

113
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,460
You came.

114
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:50,530
If someone fresh
out of police custody...

115
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:52,200
says it's urgent and about Min Jun,

116
00:09:52,260 --> 00:09:53,630
I can't exactly brush it off.

117
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:04,210
I'm sure you didn't call this late
to talk about the canceled wedding.

118
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,810
So why are you here this late?

119
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:10,280
Park Min Jun is investigating
the seven-year-old Temi Bio case.

120
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:12,080
What did you say?

121
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:16,720
He asked my father
about the merger...

122
00:10:17,190 --> 00:10:19,320
and wondered
if Baek Jun Gi's car crash...

123
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,620
was really an accident.

124
00:10:22,190 --> 00:10:23,390
It's just a gut feeling,

125
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,800
but I think
he suspects the chairman.

126
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:29,270
Min Jun suspects Chairman Park?

127
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:32,170
Why?

128
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:37,340
How did he end up
suspecting the chairman?

129
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:39,940
Well,

130
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:42,450
I'm not sure myself.

131
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:46,920
Why are you bringing this up
at this hour?

132
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:50,350
Because I haven't given up
on Min Jun yet.

133
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:54,230
It would be a loss for him
to anger the chairman over this.

134
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:56,860
If he gets caught
suspecting the chairman,

135
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:59,160
how could he possibly become
Adele's successor?

136
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:04,100
He won't listen to me,

137
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,740
so please...

138
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,140
keep Min Jun under control.

139
00:11:13,610 --> 00:11:14,610
Then...

140
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:26,460
Min Jun is looking into
what happened seven years ago,

141
00:11:27,930 --> 00:11:29,690
and he suspects Chairman Park?

142
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:38,970
When Min Jun found out who you are
and came rushing over,

143
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,240
I realized
I couldn't hide it anymore...

144
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:44,140
and that it was inevitable.

145
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:45,940
Yes.

146
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:47,950
That's what I thought.

147
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:51,050
Even so,

148
00:11:51,550 --> 00:11:54,220
despite being innocent,
he's carried a heavy burden...

149
00:11:55,290 --> 00:11:57,790
just because he's Park Tae Ho's son.

150
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,090
I want him...

151
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:03,330
to suffer even more.

152
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:05,900
Why are you saying things
you don't mean?

153
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,370
Because I want the pain
to be so overwhelming...

154
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,540
that it incapacitates him.

155
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:16,240
I'm afraid...

156
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:20,850
he'll do something
stupid and reckless...

157
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:23,280
for my sake.

158
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:26,650
I can't afford any hesitation...

159
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:30,150
that might come
from worrying about him.

160
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,560
Jin Ju,

161
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:38,630
do you still believe Chairman Park
and Choi Yu Na must die?

162
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:44,540
The law can't punish
Chairman Park Tae Ho.

163
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:47,810
So I'm going to make sure...

164
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:51,010
he dies at the hands of Choi Yu Na.

165
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:54,810
Choi Yu Na will become a murderer
for killing Park Tae Ho.

166
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:57,520
In prison, she'll wish
she were dead every single day.

167
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,550
And then...

168
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:02,750
she just might die for real.

169
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,430
One way or another,

170
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,630
I'm going to get the ending...

171
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:14,870
I want.

172
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:20,670
Even so, I still...

173
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:22,970
As your father,

174
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:25,740
I want to talk you out of this.

175
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,750
I'm sure Dr. Baek
would feel the same way.

176
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,420
Please, think this over carefully.

177
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:42,430
Please.

178
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:02,450
(Park Min Jun,
Adele's Head of Division 1)

179
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:05,750
No one can stand in the way...

180
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,050
of the ending I want.

181
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:13,990
Not James. Not my dad.

182
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,600
And not even you.

183
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:32,440
And how are you going to do that?

184
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:35,850
What could you possibly do?

185
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:43,920
After all,

186
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:46,620
you're nothing
but Chairman Park Tae Ho's son.

187
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:09,480
Why are you home so late?

188
00:15:10,050 --> 00:15:11,580
We need to talk.

189
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:14,490
Min Jun.

190
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:22,460
Min Jun.

191
00:15:24,460 --> 00:15:25,930
What is it?

192
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:27,630
Chairman Park.

193
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:35,710
Min Jun.

194
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:37,310
Don't do this.

195
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:39,210
No, let him talk.

196
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:42,210
This must be important enough
to wake a man up.

197
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:46,050
I might as well hear
what he has to say.

198
00:15:46,450 --> 00:15:47,450
Min Jun.

199
00:15:48,620 --> 00:15:49,990
Why did I...

200
00:15:50,790 --> 00:15:52,790
have to be
Chairman Park Tae Ho's son?

201
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:57,260
What?

202
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:02,530
I no longer wish to be your son.

203
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:05,140
I'm leaving the company
and this family behind.

204
00:16:05,140 --> 00:16:06,770
Right here,

205
00:16:07,810 --> 00:16:10,770
right now, I'm cutting all ties.

206
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,440
Min Jun, wait.

207
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:14,240
You little brat.

208
00:16:14,780 --> 00:16:16,680
What is this nonsense?

209
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:19,250
I said I don't want to be
your son anymore!

210
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,590
How dare you get cheeky with me?

211
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:28,560
What in the world happened
to make him act like this?

212
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,100
I'm sorry, sir.

213
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,360
Don't blame my mother for this.

214
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:36,500
This is entirely on you, not her!

215
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,840
How dare you, you little brat?

216
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,440
Sir, please.

217
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:56,090
Is something going on in there?

218
00:16:57,890 --> 00:17:01,590
It's the chairman and Mr. Min Jun.

219
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:04,500
Min Jun?

220
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,730
I've spent my whole life
walking on eggshells...

221
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,500
around your so-called greatness.

222
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,000
Not because I was scared
or intimidated,

223
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:13,870
but because
you're filthy and disgusting.

224
00:17:14,570 --> 00:17:16,910
I always wondered
why being around you felt...

225
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,410
so repulsive and agonizing,

226
00:17:20,610 --> 00:17:23,280
but now I finally understand
the sickening stench...

227
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:26,450
that comes from you.

228
00:17:27,620 --> 00:17:28,920
The reek of dirty money...

229
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:32,160
and the stench of spilled blood.

230
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:40,630
You'd better start making sense.
What is it that you think you know?

231
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:43,870
Don't you already know
what this is about?

232
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,400
In fact,

233
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:47,440
you should know.

234
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:51,810
You need to remember your crimes!

235
00:17:51,810 --> 00:17:53,040
Park Min Jun!

236
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:58,550
I'm no longer Adele's successor,
nor am I your son.

237
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,620
I'm done.

238
00:18:01,850 --> 00:18:03,020
And that's final.

239
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,520
- Hey!
- Min Jun.

240
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:07,590
That darn...

241
00:18:08,730 --> 00:18:11,800
What the heck was he going on about?

242
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:13,360
What's gotten into him?

243
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:18,740
I'm not sure either.

244
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:27,140
Hey, what's with you
all of a sudden?

245
00:18:27,210 --> 00:18:28,250
It's because of that thing.

246
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:30,950
The thing you brushed off
as frivolous.

247
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:36,290
I found out the truth.

248
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:40,520
I also found out
that neither of us deserves this.

249
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:42,990
What?

250
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:56,310
Forget the wedding.
Find the truth first.

251
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,940
If you act like a coward now,

252
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,750
you'll be no different from him.

253
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:14,490
Min Jun.

254
00:19:30,410 --> 00:19:31,410
Min Jun!

255
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:38,420
You should go back inside.

256
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:43,850
I heard everything from Ms. Choi.

257
00:19:45,020 --> 00:19:46,160
You've been looking into...

258
00:19:46,420 --> 00:19:48,830
the Temi Bio case
from seven years ago.

259
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:52,400
I don't know what you've found,

260
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,230
but confronting
your father like this...

261
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:55,300
Why...

262
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:02,010
Why did someone like Park Tae Ho...

263
00:20:03,610 --> 00:20:05,510
have to be my father?

264
00:20:08,850 --> 00:20:11,780
Every time I'm reminded
that I'm Park Tae Ho's son,

265
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:13,850
I feel like I'm going insane.

266
00:20:13,850 --> 00:20:15,320
The thought of his blood...

267
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,460
running through my veins
is so horrifying,

268
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,760
that I can't breathe in this house
for even a second.

269
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:24,900
It's so repulsive I can't stand it!

270
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:32,900
So please,

271
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:36,910
don't try to stop me anymore.

272
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,730
(Adele)

273
00:21:03,270 --> 00:21:05,770
The person you have called
is unavailable.

274
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,140
Please try again later.

275
00:21:08,870 --> 00:21:09,870
Hey...

276
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:13,640
I'm sure he's okay,
even if he isn't answering.

277
00:21:14,810 --> 00:21:17,280
This is a huge shock for him,
so he's just feeling...

278
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:20,550
completely shattered.

279
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:26,320
You were so worried
this might happen and it did.

280
00:21:29,090 --> 00:21:31,760
How did Min Jun find out
about all this?

281
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:35,930
My best guess is Ms. Choi.

282
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:41,000
She came to me and told me
to keep Min Jun under control.

283
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:45,810
He might've uncovered the deal
between her and Park Tae Ho...

284
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,650
and started looking into it...

285
00:21:49,310 --> 00:21:51,850
or she slipped up somehow.

286
00:21:52,150 --> 00:21:56,850
Darn, that Ms. Choi is just
another Oh Jung Ran.

287
00:21:57,090 --> 00:21:58,920
The moment she got out
of police custody,

288
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,160
she started causing trouble.

289
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:03,860
What if...

290
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:07,460
Min Jun never comes back?

291
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:13,270
You can't fall apart too.

292
00:22:14,070 --> 00:22:17,370
You have to focus on what you can do
while you wait for him.

293
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:20,540
Chairman Park is going to start
investigating this immediately.

294
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:22,850
Your first priority
is hiding the fact...

295
00:22:22,850 --> 00:22:24,750
that Min Jun knows everything.

296
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:26,650
You're right.

297
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:30,820
He's probably suspicious already.
I have to make up a story.

298
00:22:32,090 --> 00:22:33,460
If Chairman Park finds out,

299
00:22:34,860 --> 00:22:36,930
he won't spare Min Jun,
even if he's his own son.

300
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:45,370
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

301
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:54,510
Now I finally understand
the sickening stench...

302
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:56,910
that comes from you.

303
00:22:56,910 --> 00:22:58,180
The reek of dirty money...

304
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:00,150
and the stench of spilled blood.

305
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:01,420
You should know.

306
00:23:02,620 --> 00:23:05,790
You need to remember your crimes!

307
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:10,460
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

308
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:17,730
Remember my crimes?

309
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,640
He's cutting ties with me?

310
00:23:22,210 --> 00:23:25,010
Why would he suddenly
lash out like that?

311
00:23:31,450 --> 00:23:34,280
We haven't been able to locate
Director Park Min Jun.

312
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:36,550
Where was he yesterday?

313
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:40,790
We confirmed he was
with Choi Yu Na last night.

314
00:23:42,190 --> 00:23:43,630
Just as I thought.

315
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:46,300
Get Choi Yu Na in here right now!

316
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:48,130
Yes, sir.

317
00:23:48,770 --> 00:23:51,900
What? That brat Park Min Jun
ran away from home?

318
00:23:52,470 --> 00:23:53,600
Why?

319
00:23:53,670 --> 00:23:55,210
How should I know?

320
00:23:57,870 --> 00:24:01,310
All I know is that he left
after arguing with Chairman Park.

321
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:02,780
They fought and he left?

322
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:06,180
I'd be grateful if he'd just left.

323
00:24:06,380 --> 00:24:07,620
But they argued on top of that?

324
00:24:08,220 --> 00:24:10,990
Hey. Go get the car. Now.

325
00:24:12,390 --> 00:24:14,790
This is exactly why
I didn't want to tell you.

326
00:24:16,630 --> 00:24:18,930
Don't go stirring up trouble,

327
00:24:19,060 --> 00:24:21,570
and please stay put.

328
00:24:21,770 --> 00:24:23,430
Stay put? As if.

329
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:27,770
How can I sit back when Tae Ho
and Min Jun argued?

330
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,440
I need to find out
what they fought about,

331
00:24:30,540 --> 00:24:33,040
so I can pour gasoline on the fire.

332
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:36,810
Once we get rid of Min Jun,
Kim Myung Hui is done for.

333
00:24:37,110 --> 00:24:39,450
Then, Hyun Jun will take over Adele.

334
00:24:40,950 --> 00:24:43,150
Hurry up. Get going.

335
00:24:52,730 --> 00:24:54,830
I think I need to switch doctors.

336
00:24:55,870 --> 00:24:57,800
This medicine isn't working at all.

337
00:24:57,800 --> 00:25:02,040
Actually, I happened to find
a powerful remedy.

338
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:15,520
Hey, what's this?

339
00:25:16,990 --> 00:25:18,290
Are you crazy?

340
00:25:18,860 --> 00:25:20,820
I've been baptized.

341
00:25:21,190 --> 00:25:24,490
Oh, for goodness' sake.
Whether it's spirits or a deity,

342
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:27,800
if they both help you heal,
you get the best of both worlds.

343
00:25:27,930 --> 00:25:31,500
This sickness in your gut is caused
by those dead folks,

344
00:25:31,670 --> 00:25:34,300
so let this talisman
drive them away.

345
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:38,010
I paid a fortune for this
from a powerful shaman,

346
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:40,810
so just shut it and hold still.
Give it here.

347
00:25:43,580 --> 00:25:45,820
I have to put this on just right.

348
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:47,450
Are you kidding me?

349
00:25:48,790 --> 00:25:50,520
Now, what do I do...

350
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:52,620
- with this one?
- For crying out loud.

351
00:25:53,490 --> 00:25:54,860
What's that one for?

352
00:25:55,130 --> 00:25:57,630
This is for Yu Na.

353
00:25:57,630 --> 00:26:00,100
She's been back and forth
to the police station...

354
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,430
and has been through a lot.

355
00:26:01,730 --> 00:26:03,700
We have to take precautions.

356
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,140
But...

357
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:08,740
I'm supposed to bury this
at a specific spot...

358
00:26:09,210 --> 00:26:11,880
for it to properly ward off
evil spirits.

359
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:13,110
Bury it?

360
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:14,910
Where?

361
00:26:15,850 --> 00:26:17,250
Well, it's...

362
00:26:21,350 --> 00:26:26,990
(Park Tae Ho)

363
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,200
Right.

364
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:38,170
They told me to bury this...

365
00:26:38,170 --> 00:26:41,870
in the yard of the wretched family
tormenting our Yu Na.

366
00:26:43,010 --> 00:26:46,380
But if I can't get into the yard,

367
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,040
how can I bury this?

368
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:51,950
Got it.

369
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:56,550
If I can't bury it in the ground,
I'll just shove it into the wall.

370
00:27:04,030 --> 00:27:05,630
Goodness me. What?

371
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,560
What are you doing here
looking like that?

372
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:10,970
Well, you see, I...

373
00:27:10,970 --> 00:27:13,400
Isn't that a talisman in her hand?

374
00:27:13,740 --> 00:27:15,510
What? A talisman?

375
00:27:16,570 --> 00:27:17,640
Oh, dear.

376
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:20,940
Are you trying to curse our home
by planting this here?

377
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:23,850
You're one to talk, you witch.

378
00:27:24,580 --> 00:27:28,790
We're the ones who are cursed,
not this pathetic house of yours!

379
00:27:29,450 --> 00:27:32,520
Our Yu Na got dragged
into the police station.

380
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,820
And what about her father?

381
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:37,060
He was finally starting to recover,

382
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:41,530
but your eldest son, Park Min Jun,
came and stirred things up.

383
00:27:41,730 --> 00:27:43,930
Now he's sick in bed all over again.

384
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:48,170
Why on earth did he have to bring up
what happened seven years ago?

385
00:27:48,610 --> 00:27:53,540
My husband still has a meltdown
just hearing the name Temi Bio!

386
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:55,550
- Temi Bio?
- Temi Bio?

387
00:27:57,950 --> 00:27:58,950
That's right!

388
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:05,620
He just shows up asking about
the late CEO Baek of all people.

389
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:09,390
Now you see
why I say we've been cursed.

390
00:28:10,030 --> 00:28:11,130
Unbelievable.

391
00:28:11,930 --> 00:28:14,030
Because of you, I couldn't
even properly perform the ritual.

392
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:17,430
Seriously.
Once an enemy, always an enemy.

393
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:18,800
Wait, hold on a second.

394
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:22,470
So you're saying
Min Jun went all the way there...

395
00:28:22,770 --> 00:28:24,010
caused a scene over Temi Bio,

396
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:26,580
and even started asking
about dead people?

397
00:28:26,910 --> 00:28:27,910
Exactly.

398
00:28:30,050 --> 00:28:31,110
That's exactly what he did!

399
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:33,880
Darn.

400
00:28:38,290 --> 00:28:41,220
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

401
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:44,130
Have you taken care
of the police investigation?

402
00:28:45,860 --> 00:28:48,730
I'm still debating
whether to make it disappear.

403
00:28:49,530 --> 00:28:51,200
He's acting like his usual self.

404
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:53,900
That means Min Jun
hasn't said a word.

405
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:57,940
Just as I thought.
Using President Kim worked.

406
00:28:58,740 --> 00:29:00,680
Things can go sideways at any time,

407
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:02,980
so I have to get as much as I can
while I can.

408
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:08,380
I know you're busy,
but please hurry.

409
00:29:08,820 --> 00:29:11,420
I'm not exactly in a position
to wait patiently.

410
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:15,530
(Park Min Jun)

411
00:29:15,530 --> 00:29:18,500
I keep getting tempted
to tell Min Jun everything...

412
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:23,270
and drag us all down together.

413
00:29:25,300 --> 00:29:26,400
Is that why...

414
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:28,970
you met with him?

415
00:29:30,110 --> 00:29:32,380
I heard you were together
last night.

416
00:29:34,410 --> 00:29:35,410
We just...

417
00:29:36,350 --> 00:29:37,750
had a few drinks, that's all.

418
00:29:39,150 --> 00:29:41,480
You didn't get drunk
and let something slip,

419
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:43,520
did you?

420
00:29:44,190 --> 00:29:45,390
Do you take me for a fool?

421
00:29:46,090 --> 00:29:49,460
I have too much to lose
to make a mistake like that.

422
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:52,000
Once the police investigation is
out of the way,

423
00:29:52,260 --> 00:29:54,460
I'm going after
the Adele shares too.

424
00:29:56,030 --> 00:29:58,370
What? The Adele shares?

425
00:29:59,540 --> 00:30:01,970
You already took the voice recording
from me, sir.

426
00:30:02,370 --> 00:30:04,270
I think this is fair compensation.

427
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:08,710
Now that the recording is gone,
I think those shares...

428
00:30:09,850 --> 00:30:11,710
will make excellent leverage.

429
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:18,820
So you're telling me
you didn't say a single word...

430
00:30:19,620 --> 00:30:20,760
to my son?

431
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:24,290
If I had, do you really think
I'd be standing here right now?

432
00:30:24,630 --> 00:30:26,900
Right.
You'd have to have a death wish...

433
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:28,830
to even try.

434
00:30:32,970 --> 00:30:35,970
If you're worried
Min Jun might find something out,

435
00:30:36,610 --> 00:30:38,580
then you'd better
handle this quickly.

436
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,080
I won't wait much longer.

437
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:56,930
I'm sure he's found out about
what happened seven years ago.

438
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:00,360
But it wasn't through Choi Yu Na.

439
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:03,370
Honey!

440
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:20,680
Sir.

441
00:31:29,230 --> 00:31:30,230
Sir?

442
00:31:30,790 --> 00:31:33,160
These documents are
from Min Jun's office.

443
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:35,800
He was investigating
what happened seven years ago...

444
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:38,570
involving Temi Bio.

445
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:40,700
Why?

446
00:31:41,970 --> 00:31:43,040
That's...

447
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:46,780
Why is he digging up something
that's over and done with?

448
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:49,510
Does this have something to do...

449
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:51,250
with him throwing a fit...

450
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:53,980
and saying he doesn't want
to be my son anymore?

451
00:31:56,820 --> 00:31:58,450
What did Min Jun find out?

452
00:31:58,450 --> 00:32:00,120
And what do you know?

453
00:32:01,790 --> 00:32:02,990
Spit it out.

454
00:32:37,930 --> 00:32:40,800
(Pearl in Red)

455
00:32:41,060 --> 00:32:43,330
How dare you frame my Min Jun?

456
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:46,240
Frame him?
I was just telling the truth.

457
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:49,570
Min Jun knows about the incident
from seven years ago, doesn't he?

458
00:32:49,770 --> 00:32:52,080
Please tell me
you didn't get caught.

459
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:53,110
- My goodness!
- Do you think...

460
00:32:53,110 --> 00:32:55,480
I'm still intimidated
by Chairman Park?

461
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:57,810
The more he pushes,
the harder I'll push back...

462
00:32:57,810 --> 00:33:00,120
until I get everything I want.

463
00:33:00,180 --> 00:33:01,920
- Just you watch.
- What's all this?

464
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:04,850
Father was behind the car accident
from seven years ago?

465
00:33:04,890 --> 00:33:06,190
Jin Ju's father...

466
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:08,560
So it wasn't an accident,
but a targeted hit?

467
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,560
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
